    displayOrder: 23,
    title: 'POSH Act or Prevention of Sexual Harassment at workplace',
    description:
      '<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="color: #333333;">POSH Act or&#10;Prevention of Sexual Harassment at workplace</span></b></p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal">Ray Business Technologies Pvt Ltd is an equal opportunity employer and&#10;treats all associates equally and is committed to provide a safe environment&#10;for all its associates free from discrimination on any ground and from&#10;harassment at work including Sexual Harassment. As a Company, we are committed&#10;to conducting and governing ourselves with ethics, transparency and&#10;accountability and to this, we have developed governance structures, practices&#10;and procedures that ensure that ethical conduct at all levels is promoted&#10;across our value chain. It is thus in acknowledgement of and consonance with&#10;these values, that we are dedicated to ensuring that the work environment at our&#10;premises is conducive to fair, safe and harmonious relations, based on the mutual&#10;trust and respect, between all the associates of the Company. We also strive to&#10;guarantee a safe and welcoming environment to all those who visit our premises&#10;such as customers, vendors etc. Discrimination and harassment of any type is&#10;strictly prohibited. We wish to promote and maintain this culture to ensure&#10;that associates of the Company do not engage in any practices that are abusive&#10;in any form or manner whatsoever. </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal">The Company aims to provide a safe working environment and prohibits&#10;any form of sexual harassment. Hence any act of sexual harassment or related&#10;retaliation against or by any associate is unacceptable. </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal">Making a false complaint of sexual harassment or providing false&#10;information regarding a complaint will also be treated as a violation of&#10;policy. </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal">The Company operates a zero-tolerance policy for any form of&#10;Sexual Harassment at Workplace, deals with all incidents seriously and promptly&#10;investigates all allegations of Sexual Harassment. </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Definition of Sexual&#10;Harassment?</b></p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal">Sexual harassment includes any one or more of the following&#10;unwelcome acts or behavior (whether directly or by implication) namely:- </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst">(i)<span>                 &#10;</span>physical contact and advances; or </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle">(ii)<span>               &#10;</span>a demand or request for sexual favors; or </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle">(iii)<span>              &#10;</span>making sexually colored remarks; or </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle">(iv)<span>             &#10;</span>showing pornography; or </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoListParagraphCxSpLast">(v)<span>               &#10;</span> any other&#10;unwelcome physical, verbal, or non-verbal conduct of sexual nature.</p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> <b>Internal Complaints Committee&#10;(ICC)</b></p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> </p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal">The Company shall have a Internal Complaints Committee (“ICC”) to&#10;specifically address any complaints of sexual harassment. Below are the ICC&#10;members</p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> </p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>ICC Members are:</b></p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"></p><ol><li> <span>Roopaly Ganguly – 9000046103</span><br/></li><li> Elizabeth Arland – 9059561934<br/></li><li> Swapna Naryandas - 7396250675<br/></li><li> Jagadish Muddamsetty – 9949659655<br/></li><li> Nithin Polam – 9000255145<br/></li><li>  External member from amongst non-governmental&#10;organizations or a lawyer<br/></li></ol><p></p>&#10;&#10;<p class="MsoNormal"> <span>If any Associate believes that (s)/he has been&#10;subjected to sexual harassment, such Aggrieved Associate may file a written&#10;complaint with any member of the Committee or can send email to ICC members. Company&#10;will promptly investigate all complaints and take appropriate action, up to and&#10;including termination of employment</span></p>',
